\'\']\r\nPatent No. US 9.255,912 (<a href=\"https://patents.google.com/patent/US9255912B2/en\" target=\"_blank\">Link</a>) \"Monolithic FBAR-COS structure such as for mass sensing,\" Feb 9, 2016\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 9,217,727 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/1-1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Systems and methods for single-molecule detection using nanopores,\" December 22, 2015.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 9,194,801 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/US9194801.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Systems and methods for a DNA-based thermometer,\" Nov. 24, 2015.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 8,735,209 B2 (<a href=\"https://www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu/patents/US8735209.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Graphene device including a PVA layer or formed using a PVA layer,\" May 27, 2014.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 8,445,893 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/US8445893.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"High-Performance gate oxides such as for graphene field-effect transistors or carbon nanotubes,\" May 21, 2013.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 7,880,551 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/US7880551B2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>) \"Systems and methods for distributing a clock signal, \" Feb 1, 2011.\r\n\r\nPatent US 7,738,086 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/03/US7738086.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Active CMOS biosensor chip for fluorescent-based detection,\" Jun. 15, 2010.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 7,329,968 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/patent1.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Charge-Recycling Voltage Domains for Energy-Efficient Low-Voltage Operation of Digital CMOS Circuits,\" February 12, 2008.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 7,145,408 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/patent2.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Resonant Clock Distribution for Very Large Scale Integrated Circuits,\" December 5, 2006.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 7,103,522 B1 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/patent3.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Methods for Estimating the Body Voltage of Digital Partially Depleted Silicon-on-Insulator Circuits,\" September 5, 2006.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 7,015,765 B2 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/patent4.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Resonant Clock Distribution for Very Large Scale Integrated Circuits,\" March 21, 2006.\r\n\r\nPatent No. US 6,453,444 B1 (<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/patent5.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">PDF</a>), \"Method for Extraction of Inductances in Integrated Circuits,\" September 17, 2002.\r\n[/av_textblock]','Patents','','publish','closed','closed','','patents','','','2017-04-10 22:04:32','2017-04-10 22:04:32','',0,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/?page_id=18',0,'page','',0),(19,1,'2017-03-28 15:57:51','2017-03-28 15:57:51','','Patents','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-revision-v1','','','2017-03-28 15:57:51','2017-03-28 15:57:51','',18,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/2017/03/28/18-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(20,1,'2017-03-28 15:58:07','2017-03-28 15:58:07','[av_heading heading=\'POSITIONS AVAILABLE\' tag=\'h3\' style=\'\' size=\'\' subheading_active=\'\' subheading_size=\'15\' padding=\'10\' color=\'\' custom_font=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\'][/av_heading]\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']\r\n<p class=\"h1\"><strong>Postdoctoral Research Associate Positions Available</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\">The Bioelectronics Laboratory at Columbia University (<a href=\"http://www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu\" target=\"_blank\">www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu</a>) seeks to hire several postdoctoral fellows to work on new projects funded by the BRAIN Initiative, both by NIH and DARPA.  Projects involve the use of advanced electronic technologies, specifically, complementary metal oxide semiconductor (CMOS) technologies to interface to the brain.   Techniques include photoacoustics, ultrasound, highly scaled electrophysiology, and implanted optoelectronic devices.  Confirmation is provided with advanced microscopy, including confocal and two-photon. In all cases, we are designing and building new interface devices in deeply scaled and flexible form factors and performing <em>in vivo</em> experiments in the mouse model.  At least one project involves translating devices to non-human primates and eventually to humans.  The work in our group involves collaboration with some of the world\'s leading neuroscience groups as well as connections with industrial partners in the semiconductor and medical electronics industry.</p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\">Successful postdoctoral fellows will come from either an electronics background, with an interest in learning more about neuroscience, or a neuroscience background, with an interest in working with cutting-edge, experimental technologies for interfacing to the BRAIN. Experience in mouse-model electrophysiology, optical microscopy, integrated circuit design, or microfabrication is a plus.</p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\">Postdoctoral positions will be for at least two years with an option for an additional year.  We offer a very competitive salary and housing assistance.</p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\">Interested candidates should send their CV and the names of three references to Prof. Ken Shepard (<a href=\"mailto:shepard@ee.columbia.edu\" target=\"_blank\">shepard@ee.columbia.edu</a>).</p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\"><strong>Doctoral Students</strong></p>\r\n<p class=\"h1\">I generally take M. S./Ph. D. students for Fall admission only who apply to either electrical engineering or biomedical engineering. (I review applications in both of these departments.) I will also consider students from other departments, although I will not be reviewing applications there. Students who wish to make sure I review their application are welcome to contact me at <a href=\"mailto:shepard@ee.columbia.edu\">shepard@ee.columbia.edu</a>. If you are applying to a department other than EE or BME, you must contact me or I will not review your application. Admission deadline is December 15.</p>\r\n[/av_textblock]','Positions Available','','publish','closed','closed','','positions-available','','','2017-04-10 22:06:33','2017-04-10 22:06:33','',0,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/?page_id=20',0,'page','',0),(21,1,'2017-03-28 15:58:07','2017-03-28 15:58:07','','Positions Available','','inherit','closed','closed','','20-revision-v1','','','2017-03-28 15:58:07','2017-03-28 15:58:07','',20,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/2017/03/28/20-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(22,1,'2017-04-03 07:24:07','2017-04-03 07:24:07','[av_heading heading=\'PATENTS\' tag=\'h3\' style=\'\' size=\'\' subheading_active=\'\' subheading_size=\'15\' padding=\'10\' color=\'\' custom_font=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\'][/av_heading]\n\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\nClick here to add your own text\n[/av_textblock]\n\n','Patents','','inherit','closed','closed','','18-autosave-v1','','','2017-04-03 07:24:07','2017-04-03 07:24:07','',18,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/2017/03/29/18-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(75,1,'2017-04-03 07:25:33','2017-04-03 07:25:33','','1-1','','inherit','open','closed','','1-1','','','2017-04-03 07:25:33','2017-04-03 07:25:33','',0,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/1-1.pdf',0,'attachment','application/pdf',0),(24,1,'2017-03-30 23:36:43','2017-03-30 23:36:43','{\n    \"show_on_front\": {\n        \"value\": \"page\",\n        \"type\": \"option\",\n        \"user_id\": 1\n    },\n    \"page_on_front\": {\n        \"value\": \"2\",\n        \"type\": \"option\",\n        \"user_id\": 1\n    }\n}','','','trash','closed','closed','','b92737cc-786a-4bc2-a757-70e250d64fde','','','2017-03-30 23:36:43','2017-03-30 23:36:43','',0,'http://bioee.academicwebpages.com/2017/03/30/b92737cc-786a-4bc2-a757-70e250d64fde/',0,'customize_changeset','',0),(25,1,'2017-03-30 23:48:14','2017-03-30 23:48:14','[av_layerslider id=\'1\']\r\n\r\n[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0